=Short bio=

Janice Figueiredo is a multiligual Brazilian commons activist interested in the areas of collective intelligence, collaborative movements, P2P dynamics, the Commons, the open and sharing society, social business, complementary currencies, sustainable development and poverty reduction, with particular interest in exploring alternative models to the conventional economic paradigms based on centralization and scarcity.

*contact: janicefigueiredo@gmail.com

=Recent research activities=

* Commons Transition - http://commonstransition.org 
* Flok Society Project - Research Coordinator on 'Open Infrastructures for Collective Life' - http://floksociety.org
* Grupo de Pesquisa P2P no Brasil (Collaborative Economy and P2P Production Research Group in Brazil)  

